# Admin Panel Enhancements — User Management, Subscription Control, Financial Overview

## Context
The admin panel currently has: dashboard, schools CRUD, plans CRUD, payment requests (verify/reject), and settings.
Three high-priority gaps need filling: user management across schools, subscription lifecycle control, and a financial overview.

## Existing Patterns (from codebase analysis)
- **Controller pattern**: Resource controllers in `App\Http\Controllers\Admin\`, extend `Controller`, filter via `$request->filled()`, paginate 15 with `->appends($request->query())`
- **View pattern**: `@extends('layouts.admin')`, `@section('title')`, `@section('subtitle')`, `@section('content')`
- **Card style**: `bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm`, animate-fade-up with delay-N
- **Status badges**: Color-coded pills with dot indicator
- **Role badges**: purple=owner, blue=admin, cyan=teacher, emerald=student, amber=parent
- **Stat cards**: Gradient top bar + gradient icon container
- **Sidebar nav**: Section headers + `sidebar-link` with `data-tooltip`/`data-nav-text`, active via `request()->routeIs()`
- **Mail pattern**: `Mail::to($user->email)->queue(new MailableClass($model))`
- **DB transactions**: Used for multi-model operations
- **Models**: `$fillable`, `casts()` method, relationship methods, helper booleans (`isActive()`, `isPending()`), accessors (`getFormattedAmountAttribute`)

---

## Feature 1: User Management

### 1.1 Routes (add to admin group in `routes/web.php`)
```php
Route::resource('users', UserController::class)->except(['create', 'store']);
Route::post('users/{user}/toggle-active', [UserController::class, 'toggleActive'])->name('users.toggle-active');
```
No create/store — admins don't create users; schools manage their own.

### 1.2 Controller: `app/Http/Controllers/Admin/UserController.php`
```php
class UserController extends Controller
{
    public function index(Request $request)
    {
        $query = User::with('school')->where('role', '!=', 'super_admin');

        if ($request->filled('school')) {
            $query->where('school_id', $request->school);
        }
        if ($request->filled('role')) {
            $query->where('role', $request->role);
        }
        if ($request->filled('search')) {
            $search = $request->search;
            $query->where(function ($q) use ($search) {
                $q->where('first_name', 'like', "%{$search}%")
                  ->orWhere('last_name', 'like', "%{$search}%")
                  ->orWhere('email', 'like', "%{$search}%");
            });
        }

        $users = $query->latest()->paginate(15)->appends($request->query());
        $schools = School::orderBy('name')->pluck('name', 'id'); // for filter dropdown

        return view('admin.users.index', compact('users', 'schools'));
    }

    public function show(User $user)
    {
        $user->load('school');
        return view('admin.users.show', compact('user'));
    }

    public function toggleActive(Request $request, User $user)
    {
        if ($user->role === 'super_admin') {
            return back()->with('error', 'Cannot modify super admin accounts.');
        }

        $user->update(['is_active' => !$user->is_active]);

        return back()->with('success', "User {$user->full_name} has been " . ($user->is_active ? 'activated' : 'deactivated') . ".");
    }
}
```

### 1.3 Views

**`resources/views/admin/users/index.blade.php`**
- Page header "Users" with subtitle
- Filter bar: search input, school dropdown, role dropdown, filter button
- Table: Avatar+name | Email | School | Role badge | Status badge (Active/Inactive) | Actions (View, Activate/Deactivate)
- Pagination links
- Empty state

**`resources/views/admin/users/show.blade.php`**
- Back link to users index
- User hero card: avatar, name, email, role badge, school link
- Detail grid: School, Joined date, Last seen, Status, Class/Section (if student)
- Action button: Activate/Deactivate

### 1.4 Sidebar nav (in `layouts/admin.blade.php`, Management section, after Schools)
```html
<a href="{{ route('admin.users.index') }}" data-tooltip="Users" data-nav-text="Users"
   class="sidebar-link {{ request()->routeIs('admin.users.*') ? 'active' : 'text-slate-600' }}">
    <svg ...users icon...></svg>
    <span class="sidebar-text">Users</span>
    <span class="sidebar-badge ml-auto text-[10px] font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-600">{{ \App\Models\User::where('role', '!=', 'super_admin')->count() }}</span>
</a>
```

---

## Feature 2: Subscription Control

### 2.1 Routes (add to admin group)
```php
Route::post('schools/{school}/extend-trial', [SchoolController::class, 'extendTrial'])->name('schools.extend-trial');
Route::post('schools/{school}/activate', [SchoolController::class, 'activateSubscription'])->name('schools.activate');
Route::post('schools/{school}/suspend', [SchoolController::class, 'suspend'])->name('schools.suspend');
```

### 2.2 Controller methods (add to existing `SchoolController.php`)
```php
public function extendTrial(Request $request, School $school)
{
    $validated = $request->validate([
        'days' => 'required|integer|min:1|max:365',
    ]);

    $newTrialEnd = $school->trial_ends_at
        ? $school->trial_ends_at->addDays($validated['days'])
        : now()->addDays($validated['days']);

    $school->update([
        'subscription_status' => 'trial',
        'trial_ends_at' => $newTrialEnd,
    ]);

    // Update or create latest trial subscription
    $subscription = $school->subscriptions()->where('status', 'trial')->latest()->first();
    if ($subscription) {
        $subscription->update(['trial_ends_at' => $newTrialEnd]);
    }

    return back()->with('success', "Trial extended by {$validated['days']} days for {$school->name}.");
}

public function activateSubscription(Request $request, School $school)
{
    $validated = $request->validate([
        'plan_id' => 'required|exists:plans,id',
        'billing_cycle' => 'required|in:monthly,yearly',
    ]);

    $startsAt = now();
    $endsAt = $validated['billing_cycle'] === 'yearly'
        ? $startsAt->copy()->addYear()
        : $startsAt->copy()->addMonth();

    DB::transaction(function () use ($school, $validated, $startsAt, $endsAt) {
        // Cancel any existing active subscription
        $school->subscriptions()->where('status', 'active')->update([
            'status' => 'canceled',
            'canceled_at' => now(),
        ]);

        Subscription::create([
            'school_id' => $school->id,
            'plan_id' => $validated['plan_id'],
            'status' => 'active',
            'billing_cycle' => $validated['billing_cycle'],
            'starts_at' => $startsAt,
            'ends_at' => $endsAt,
        ]);

        $school->update([
            'subscription_status' => 'active',
            'plan_id' => $validated['plan_id'],
        ]);
    });

    return back()->with('success', "Subscription activated for {$school->name} until {$endsAt->format('M j, Y')}.");
}

public function suspend(Request $request, School $school)
{
    $validated = $request->validate([
        'reason' => 'nullable|string|max:500',
    ]);

    DB::transaction(function () use ($school, $validated) {
        $school->subscriptions()->where('status', 'active')->update([
            'status' => 'canceled',
            'canceled_at' => now(),
        ]);

        $school->update(['subscription_status' => 'expired']);
    });

    return back()->with('success', "Subscription suspended for {$school->name}.");
}
```

### 2.3 View: Add subscription control card to `resources/views/admin/schools/show.blade.php`
New card below the existing stats row, titled "Subscription Management":
- Current status badge (trial/active/expired)
- If trial: "Extend Trial" form (days input + submit button)
- "Manually Activate" form (plan dropdown + billing cycle select + submit)
- "Suspend Subscription" form (reason textarea + submit, with confirm dialog)
- Show current subscription details: plan name, billing cycle, start date, end date

---

## Feature 3: Financial Overview

### 3.1 Routes (add to admin group)
```php
Route::get('finance', [FinanceController::class, 'index'])->name('finance.index');
```

### 3.2 Controller: `app/Http/Controllers/Admin/FinanceController.php`
```php
class FinanceController extends Controller
{
    public function index(Request $request)
    {
        // Revenue from verified payment requests
        $totalRevenue = PaymentRequest::where('status', 'verified')->sum('amount');
        $monthlyRevenue = PaymentRequest::where('status', 'verified')
            ->whereMonth('verified_at', now()->month)
            ->whereYear('verified_at', now()->year)
            ->sum('amount');
        $yearlyRevenue = PaymentRequest::where('status', 'verified')
            ->whereYear('verified_at', now()->year)
            ->sum('amount');

        // Monthly revenue for chart (last 12 months)
        $monthlyData = PaymentRequest::where('status', 'verified')
            ->where('verified_at', '>=', now()->subMonths(11)->startOfMonth())
            ->selectRaw('MONTH(verified_at) as month, YEAR(verified_at) as year, SUM(amount) as total')
            ->groupBy('year', 'month')
            ->orderBy('year')
            ->orderBy('month')
            ->get();

        // Recent transactions
        $transactions = PaymentRequest::with(['school', 'plan', 'verifier'])
            ->where('status', 'verified')
            ->latest('verified_at')
            ->paginate(15);

        // Pending amount
        $pendingAmount = PaymentRequest::where('status', 'pending')->sum('amount');

        return view('admin.finance.index', compact(
            'totalRevenue', 'monthlyRevenue', 'yearlyRevenue',
            'monthlyData', 'transactions', 'pendingAmount'
        ));
    }
}
```

### 3.3 View: `resources/views/admin/finance/index.blade.php`
- Page header "Financial Overview"
- Stat cards row: Total Revenue, This Month, This Year, Pending Amount
- Revenue trend: simple bar chart using inline SVG/divs showing last 12 months
- Transactions table: School | Plan | Billing Cycle | Amount | Verified By | Date
- Pagination

### 3.4 Sidebar nav (in Management section, after Payment Requests)
```html
<a href="{{ route('admin.finance.index') }}" data-tooltip="Finance" data-nav-text="Finance"
   class="sidebar-link {{ request()->routeIs('admin.finance.*') ? 'active' : 'text-slate-600' }}">
    <svg ...chart icon...></svg>
    <span class="sidebar-text">Finance</span>
</a>
```

---

## Implementation Order

1. **User Management** — controller, 2 views, sidebar nav link, routes
2. **Subscription Control** — 3 controller methods, show.blade.php card, routes
3. **Financial Overview** — controller, 1 view, sidebar nav link, route

## Verification
1. `php artisan view:cache` — Blade compiles without errors
2. `php artisan route:list` — All new routes registered
3. Manual checks:
   - Visit `/admin/users` → search/filter by school and role
   - Toggle a user active/inactive
   - Visit `/admin/schools/{id}` → extend trial, activate, suspend
   - Visit `/admin/finance` → verify revenue stats match verified payment requests

## Files to Create
- `app/Http/Controllers/Admin/UserController.php`
- `app/Http/Controllers/Admin/FinanceController.php`
- `resources/views/admin/users/index.blade.php`
- `resources/views/admin/users/show.blade.php`
- `resources/views/admin/finance/index.blade.php`

## Files to Modify
- `routes/web.php` — add new routes
- `app/Http/Controllers/Admin/SchoolController.php` — add extendTrial, activateSubscription, suspend methods
- `resources/views/admin/schools/show.blade.php` — add subscription management card
- `resources/views/layouts/admin.blade.php` — add Users and Finance sidebar links

